Why did you split this into two tests? 
In case it's not an ES docstore, we basically just test that passing headers doesn't throw an error? For this, the test seems quite expansive (loading in the whole pipeline etc.). 
In case it's an elastic store, we basically test the same thing as above (just this time with tf-idf)?

@author:
First one ensures all retrievers compatible with ElasticsearchDocumentStore and actually searching with es propagate the headers correctly. Second is intended to ensure that all DocumentStores can deal with the headers param. In case of ElasticsearchDocumentStore TFIDF Retriever does not 'search' with ES (e.g. call ElasticSearch's client.search()) but only calls count() on the document store. So that is also an implicit test, that not only client.search() gets the headers propagated correctly.

